1. **Node Goal**: The natural language goal "sitting down" needs the object (sofa) to transition to an "SITTING" state (from initial "CLEAN" state). This sets the node goal.
2. **Edge Goal**: Sitting implies the "character" uses the "ON" relationship (resting on the sofa), so the edge goal is created from the character to the sofa using the "ON" relation.
3. **Action Goals**: The required state transitions and relationship (edge goal) already fully cover the goal, so no additional action goals are needed.

